  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a pilot study of the safety, tolerability and efficacy of an investigational
      central venous catheter device used in conjunction with a standard central venous catheter.
      The hypothesis is that utilization of a catheter device incorporating cyanoacrylate will
      reduce catheter colonization by bacteria, and may decrease the rate of catheter-related
      bloodstream infections.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
